The paper discusses the use of probabilistic models for unsupervised clustering in text collections, which is a common topic in natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with estimation and evaluation of the model, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the high dimensionality of the parameter space, which is a common issue in many sub-fields of computer science, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
